  "title": "Marketing Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong><br />The Marketing Executive supports the planning, execution, and monitoring of marketing campaigns to promote the company’s products or services. This role focuses on increasing brand awareness, driving customer engagement, and supporting sales through effective marketing activities.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Assist in planning and executing marketing campaigns across digital and offline channels.</p></li><li><p>Create and manage marketing content, including social media posts, email campaigns, and promotional materials.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with designers, agencies, and vendors to deliver marketing assets.</p></li><li><p>Conduct basic market research and competitor analysis.</p></li><li><p>Track and report on campaign performance and marketing metrics.</p></li><li><p>Support event planning, product launches, and promotional activities.</p></li><li><p>Maintain brand consistency across all marketing communications.</p></li><li><p>Manage marketing databases, mailing lists, and CRM updates.<br /></p><p><strong>Required Skills and Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business, Communications, or a related field.</p></li><li><p>Strong written and verbal communication skills.</p></li><li><p>Basic understanding of digital marketing tools and platforms.</p></li><li><p>Creative thinking with attention to detail.</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage multiple tasks and meet deadlines.</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in MS Office and marketing tools.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><p>Experience with social media management and content creation.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with SEO, SEM, and email marketing tools.</p></li><li><p>Experience using analytics tools such as Google Analytics.</p></li><li><p>Prior internship or marketing experience.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Key Competencies</strong></p><ul><li><p>Team collaboration</p></li><li><p>Organizational skills</p></li><li><p>Creativity and initiative</p></li><li><p>Analytical thinking</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
